title: Modigliani (Abrams Art Ebook).pdf
description:
Abrams | 1954 | Pdf | Eng | 74 pag | 2 MB

The text for this volume is a perceptive and colorful reminiscence of Amedeo Modigliani by his close friend, the world-famous sculptor Jacques Lipchitz. The thirty pages of full color plates include portraits of notable artists and poets, swannecked women, delicately drawn nudes, and wistful, dreamy-eyed children. The black-and-white illustrations present a rich selection of Modigliani's drawings and
sculpture, some never before reproduced
